  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the grill to high, then add the <strong>white long grain rice </strong>to a pot with a lid with 225ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[450ml]</span> <strong>cold water </strong>and bring to a boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 12-15 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked</p><p>Once done, remove from the heat and set aside (lid on) to steam until serving</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1635260357698-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1635260357698-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1635260357698-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1635260357698-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1635260357698-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, boil half a kettle</p><p>Peel (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>ginger</strong></p><p>Add <strong>half </strong>of the <strong>chopped ginger</strong> to a large bowl with the <strong>miso paste</strong>, 1/3 of the <strong>toasted</strong> <strong>sesame oil</strong> (you'll use the rest later!) and 1 tbsp<span class=\"text-danger\"> [2 tbsp]<strong> </span>cold water</strong></p><p>Mix until smooth – this is your <strong>miso marinade</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1635260363825-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1635260363825-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1635260363825-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1635260363825-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1635260363825-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>haddock bites</strong> to the miso<strong> </strong>marinade and give them a gentle mix up until fully coated</p><p>Tip: Unevenly sized haddock bites? Chop any larger ones into bite-sized pieces!</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1635260366671-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1635260366671-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1635260366671-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1635260366671-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1635260366671-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Line a tray with <strong>tin foil</strong> and add the <strong>coated haddock bites</strong></p><p>Put the tray under the grill for 10-12 min or until the fish is cooked though and starting to char</p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked once it turns opaque and flakes easily</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1635260370259-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1635260370259-x400.jpg",
