          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1635260370259-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the haddock is cooking, cut the<strong> cucumber </strong>in half lengthways (scrape out the inner seeds with a teaspoon and discard), then dice</p><p>Add the <strong>blanched edamame beans</strong> to a colander and pour <strong>boiled water </strong>all over them to refresh them, then run under <strong>cold</strong> <strong>water</strong> until cool</p><p>Peel and slice the <strong>shallot<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> as finely as you can</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1635260373272-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1635260373272-x400.jpg",
